@NODE "Presentation" "Presentation"
@TOC "sommaire"

@{b}I  Presentation.@{ub}

 Only the menu items are in French, but don't worry, only few words are
 used and I add items translation in documentation. See @{"vocabulary" LINK "vocab"}.
 The internal messages are in English. Exept if I forgot one.  ;-)
 
 This program is an specific database design for 'mini-bar' handle and
 conception of cocktails.

 This is a very convivial one !

 
Caracteristics :  "Cocktails" version 1.25 / Copyright 92-98 @{b}Hervé Dupont@{ub}.
		  Great thanks to @{b}Vincent Texier@{ub} for imagerie.

		  Programed in Amos 1.36  Copyright @{b}François Lionet@{ub}.
      @{fg highlight}            Work an AGA computers too.
		  1 Mo minimum and hard drive strongly recommended.@{fg text}

Source is about 3500 lines long, and more than 17 000 instructions.

The Cocktails directory is made up of :

	- Cocktails         The program.

	- Cocktails_data    Main registered directory with data files

		- Bar.Default           - Cocktails.Dflt
		- Cocktails.Index       - Cocktails.Noms
		- Cocktails.Rectt       - Ingredients.Data
		- Ingredients.Index     - Exemple.Bar

	- Cocktails_data_dp Same as above, but for unregistered people.

	- Docs  Documentation directory in amigaguide format.

 This program is 'ShareWare' and it is limited at 140 ingredients and
 50 cocktails. That is efficient to have an idea about this software.

 Demo version is provided with 135 ingredients and 40 cocktails.
 The registered version is able to handle 400 ingredients and 800 cocktails,
 and it is deliver with nearby 170 ingredients and more than 280 cocktails.

 A 'big' version able to manage up to 500 ingredients and 2500 cocktails
 is available on request, but the requested configuration is 1Mo Chip +
 3 Fast minimum. (Registered people only).
 Note that normal version will can't manage database from big version if
 there are more 800 cocktails or 400 ingredients.

 See @{"Registration" LINK "regist"} section for more informations.
 
@ENDNODE

