@ENDNODE



@NODE "vocab" "Vocabulary"
@TOC "sommaire"

@{b}VII  Vocabulary and shortcuts@{ub}


@{u}@{b}Vocabulary@{ub}@{uu} :

@{u}On first screen@{uu} (Bar screen) we will find :

The 'bar' tiny picture      - Calcs and shows statistics.

Charger     = To load       - Load a saved bar from disk.
Sauver      = To save       - Save a created or modified bar on disk.
Modifier    = To modify     - Modification of bar previously loaded.
Créer       = To create     - Create a new bar. (Selection of ingredients)
Imprimer    = To print      - Print the ingredients list on printer.
Quitter     = To quit       - Go back to WorkBench.
Cocktails   -               - Go to screen cocktails.
Pages       = pages ;-)     - Up and down scroll into ingredients list.


@{u}On second screen@{uu} (Cocktails screen) we will find :

Ajouter cocktails  = to add a cocktail  - Create a new cocktail.
little window where words should be in English.
Imprimer           = Print selected cocktails.
Sélectionner       = to Select     - Choose between five show mode.
Retour au bar      = Return to previous screen. Bar screen.
Pages              = Scroll in cocktails list.

-> "Tous les cocktails"        = All cocktails.
-> "Les cocktails réalisables" = Realizable cocktails.
-> "Suivant une base"          = Base function.
-> "Les alcoolisés"            = alcoholics.
-> "Les non alcoolisés"        = non alcoholics.


@{u}On third screen@{uu} (Showing cocktails (recipe)) we will find :

Retour au menu = Return to previous screen.


@{u}@{b}Shortcuts@{ub}@{uu} :

° The right mouse button is used to confirm action or terminate action.

° Amiga + A : Swap between Cocktails programm and WorkBench. (Amos function)
  The right mouse button is often use to confirm an action.

° Mystic chars. :-)
  î -> Shift + 1 (numeric keyboard)
  ę -> Shift + 7 (num Kb)
  ű -> Shift + 9 (num Kb)

@ENDNODE



